    {
      "speaker_id": "sundar-pichai",
      "speaker_name": "Sundar Pichai",
      "speaker_role": "CEO",
      "timestamp": "00:01:00",
      "text": "Q3 was another excellent quarter. Google Cloud revenue reached $11.4 billion, up 35% year-over-year, exceeding our Q2 guidance range. Our AI infrastructure investments are paying off — we are now seeing more than 25,000 enterprises actively using Gemini models through Vertex AI. We expect Cloud to continue growing faster than 30% in Q4 and into 2025, driven by strong enterprise AI adoption."
    },
    {
      "speaker_id": "anat-ashkenazi",
      "speaker_name": "Anat Ashkenazi",
      "speaker_role": "CFO",
      "timestamp": "00:20:00",
      "text": "Total revenues were $88.3 billion, up 15% year-over-year. Google Cloud operating income was $1.95 billion, representing a 17% operating margin, expanding meaningfully year-over-year. We remain on track to deliver full-year Cloud operating margin expansion. Search revenues grew 12% to $49.4 billion, reflecting continued strength in AI-enhanced results."
    },
    {
      "speaker_id": "operator",
      "speaker_name": "Operator",
      "speaker_role": "Operator",
      "timestamp": "00:38:00",
      "text": "Our next question comes from Brent Thill at Jefferies."
    },
    {
      "speaker_id": "analyst-brent-thill",
      "speaker_name": "Brent Thill",
      "speaker_role": "Analyst",
      "timestamp": "00:38:20",
      "text": "Sundar, can you give us a sense of how AI Overviews is affecting monetization in Search, and whether you see any risk to query volume as the AI experience matures?"
    }
  ],
